cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with spiking neural networks and their behavior in the presence of noise and inaccuracies in synaptic weights. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of analog 'synaptic' devices, which falls under the category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also involves training spiking networks, which is a common topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hafnium-oxide based resistive random-access memory, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
